@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{ledger-mode-extras.el} extends @samp{ledger-mode}, the Emacs major mode
for editing plain-text accounting files compatible with the Ledger
command-line tool.  The stock mode covers basic editing and reporting,
but leaves several common workflows---importing transactions from
brokerages, adjusting transaction dates, sorting in reverse
chronological order, and fetching commodity prices---to the user.
This package fills those gaps.

The extensions are organized around six workflows:

@itemize
@item
@strong{Importing transactions} from CSV exports (Polymarket, Interactive
Brokers) and from the system clipboard (Wise Airbnb payouts)
(@ref{Importing transactions}).
@item
@strong{Navigation and editing}: creating entries, aligning amounts,
copying or killing transactions, and narrowing to a single
transaction (@ref{Navigation and editing}).
@item
@strong{Date manipulation}: incrementing or decrementing the date of the
transaction at point (@ref{Date manipulation}).
@item
@strong{Reports}: running common Ledger reports with a single command
(@ref{Reporting}).
@item
@strong{Price updates}: fetching commodity and cryptocurrency prices via
external Python scripts (@ref{Price updates}).
@item
@strong{Sorting}: sorting transactions chronologically or reverse-
chronologically, for a region or the whole buffer
(@ref{Sorting}).
@end itemize

The package depends on @samp{ledger-mode} and @samp{paths} (for file path
variables such as @code{paths-file-ledger} and @code{paths-dir-ledger}).

