@node Transaction insertion
@section Transaction insertion

@findex ledger-mode-extras-insert-transaction
The function @code{ledger-mode-extras-insert-transaction} takes a list of
FIELDS (payee, date, account, quantity, token-symbol, price, and
optional fees) and appends a formatted Ledger transaction to FILE
(defaulting to @code{paths-file-ledger}).  After inserting the transaction
lines it calls @code{ledger-mode-extras-align-and-next}
(@ref{Navigation and editing}) to align the amounts.  This function is
used by the import commands (@ref{Importing transactions}).

@node Date conversion
@section Date conversion

@findex ledger-extras-convert-interactive-brokers-date
The function @code{ledger-extras-convert-interactive-brokers-date} converts
an Interactive Brokers date string in @samp{YYYYMMDD} format to the
standard @samp{YYYY-MM-DD} format used in Ledger files.

@node Core helpers
@section Core helpers

@findex ledger-mode-extras-copy-or-kill-transaction-at-point
@findex ledger-mode-extras-increase-date
The function @code{ledger-mode-extras-copy-or-kill-transaction-at-point}
is the shared implementation behind the kill and copy commands
(@ref{Navigation and editing}).  It accepts an ACTION argument (@code{copy} or
@code{kill}) and operates on the transaction at point.

The function @code{ledger-mode-extras-increase-date} adjusts the date of
the transaction at point by a given number of DAYS (positive or
negative).  It is used by the one-day increment and decrement commands
(@ref{Date manipulation}).

